        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 3:07PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 307 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Adrian, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Adrian around 310 PM EDT.
Britton around 340 PM EDT.
Deerfield around 345 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Seneca, Macon, Ogden
Center, Ridgeway, Palmyra, Tipton, Sand Creek, Jasper, Rome Center,
and Weston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
